      <title><![CDATA[Github+Hexo[basics]]]></title>
      <url>/2017/06/12/github-hexo/</url>
      <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Hexo is a very useful tool to build static websites and it has lots of simple and beautiful themes to select. Here are few tips that I conclude: (Mac OSX)</p>
<ol>
<li>create a github account and generate ssh keys. Do not create two accounts at the same time or it will bring trouble!!</li>
<li><p>create a new respository and a new file (<code>mkdir</code>) called “blog” and follow its instructions:</p>
 <figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><div class="line">1</div><div class="line">2</div><div class="line">3</div></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><div class="line">git init</div><div class="line">git add .</div><div class="line">git commit</div></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
</li>
<li><p>install <code>node</code> and xcode</p>
</li>
<li>install hexo in “blog” file: sudo npm install -g hexo</li>
<li><p>Setup</p>
 <figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><div class="line">1</div><div class="line">2</div><div class="line">3</div></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><div class="line">hexo init</div><div class="line">  hexo generate</div><div class="line">  hexo server</div></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
</li>
<li><p>create a new respository called your_user_name.github.io</p>
</li>
<li><p>revise _config.yml file to:</p>
<figure class="highlight yaml"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><div class="line">1</div><div class="line">2</div><div class="line">3</div><div class="line">4</div></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><div class="line"><span class="attr">deploy:</span></div><div class="line"><span class="attr">  type:</span> <span class="string">git</span></div><div class="line"><span class="attr">  repo:</span> <span class="attr">https://github.com/username/username.github.io.git</span></div><div class="line"><span class="attr">  branch:</span> <span class="string">master</span></div></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
</li>
<li><p>npm install hexo-deployer-git –save</p>
</li>
<li>hexo generate</li>
<li>hexo server </li>
<li>hexo deploy</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="what-should-I-do-if-create-two-accounts"><a href="#what-should-I-do-if-create-two-accounts" class="headerlink" title="what should I do if create two accounts?"></a>what should I do if create two accounts?</h2><p>In the settings, we can transfer the respository into another account then delete one account.</p>
<h2 id="Done"><a href="#Done" class="headerlink" title="Done!"></a>Done!</h2><p><img src="http://blog.zhangruipeng.me/hexo-theme-hueman/gallery/math.jpg" alt=""></p>
]]></content>
      
